22/06/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Austria has offered to assist Macedonia in its EU integration efforts, Austrian Foreign Minister Benita Ferrero-Waldner told Macedonian counterpart Ilinka Mitreva in Skopje on Monday (21 June). Ferrero-Waldner says Austria stands ready to help with concrete projects and would provide expert assistance in completing the EC questionnaire, which Macedonia is due to receive in the fall.
Also Monday, Macedonian Army Chief of General Staff Major General Gjorgji Bojadjiev left for a three-day official visit to Germany. The focus will be bilateral co-operation, especially in regards to the international peacekeeping mission in Afghanistan. (Makfax, MIA, A1 TV - 21/06/04)
